    <description>Extract Dataverse metadata and generate Power BI TMDL/PBIP semantic models with automatic table relationships, calendar tables, and incremental change detection.</description>
    <summary>XrmToolBox plugin for generating Power BI semantic models from Dataverse metadata</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
  v1.2026.5.125 — Attribute-grid UX and expanded-field control release.

Key updates:
- Expanded child rows now have in-grid Include/Hidden toggles
- In Show: Selected mode, grouped child rows remain visible even when not included
- Added Open all groups / Collapse all groups and persisted group open/collapse state
- Expanded column now has header + count display (e.g., ▶ Expand (2)); width rebalanced to avoid truncation
- Choice numeric Include now defaults Hidden=true when enabled
- Expanded child Include now behaves as a true toggle (unchecked rows stay visible)
- Expanded Include/Hidden settings are persisted and honored during semantic model generation

Recent prior releases:
- v1.2026.5.110 — Incremental-update and output-stability fixes (description preservation scope, null-safety, lineage stability, opt-in FetchXML debug logs)
- v1.2026.5.101 — Lookup sub-column controls, polymorphic lookup support, collapsible groups, and relationship selector improvements
- v1.2026.5.84 — Fixed expanded-lookup JOINs to always use logical/schema table names

Full change history is maintained in CHANGELOG.md.
    </releaseNotes>
